Label.content: Value of the Adjust "label" parameter sent on click

PublisherParams.content: Custom publisher parameters collected by the Adjust SDK (never displayed in Adjust Dashboard)

SecretId.content: Secret ID for the SDK signature

IadAdId.content: Apple Search Ads adId (for Default Product Page, -1 is set)

IadConversionType.content: Download status: first or subsequent app download

IadCountryOrRegion.content: Apple Search Ads country or region associated with camapign.

AttributionExpiresAt.content: Unix timestamp of when the current temporary attribution expires. More details

AttributionTtl.content: Reflects the temporary attribution window of the engagement (hours). More details

CallbackTtl.content: Maximum time after the install callbacks are sent (hours)

ClickAttributionWindow.content: Attribution window settings for device matching (hours)

ImpressionAttributionWindow.content: Attribution window settings for device matching (hours)

LastFallbackTime.content: Timestamp of when the user moved to the fallback source. More details

LastFallbackTimeHour.content: Timestamp of when the user moved to the fallback source, rounded to the nearest hour. More details

Platform.content: Indicates if the activity happened on mobile or web

ProbmatchingAttributionWindow.content: Attribution window settings for probabilistic matching (hours)

ProbmatchingReattributionAttributionTTL.content: Reflects the temporary probabilistic matching reattribution window of the engagement (hours). More details

ProbmatchingReattributionAttributionWind.content: Attribution window settings for probabilistic matching reattribution (hours)

ProbmatchingReattributionFallbackType.content: Reflects the engagement's probabilistic matching reattribution fallback type. More details

ProbmatchingReattributionInactiveUserDef.content: Inactivity period required for probabilistic matching reattribution (hours)

ReattributionAttributionTtl.content: Reflects the temporary reattribution window of the engagement (hours). More details

ReattributionFallbackType.content: Reflects the engagement's reattribution fallback type. More details

WithinCallbackTtl.content: Return 0/1 value based on whether the event was triggered within or outside of the callback TTL

ActivityKind.example: impression; click; install; session; event; reattribution, uninstall, reinstall, reattribution_reinstall, rejected_install; rejected_reattribution; cost_update; gdpr_forget_device; san_click; san_impression; ad_revenue; install_update; reattribution_update; sk_install; sk_event; sk_qualifier; subscription; att_update

AdImpressionsCount.content: Number of mobile ads served to end users

AdRevenueNetwork.content: Ad network that displayed the ad

AdRevenuePlacement.content: User placement, as defined on the platform

AdRevenueUnit.content: Ad unit that generated the revenue

AdgroupName.content: Adgroup name, as taken from the tracker

AppName.content: iOS Bundle id obtained from SDK, fallback to app id filled in Adjust dashboard (iOS); package name (android)

AppNameDashboard.content: Name of the app in the Adjust Dashboard

AppVersion.content: App version number (Android); build-version-number for the bundle (iOS), a sanitised version of {app_version_raw}, fallback to 'unknown' when data is invalid

AppVersionRaw.content: App version number (Android); build-version-number for the bundle, including small patch versions (iOS)

AppVersionShort.content: App version number (Android); release-version-number for the bundle as seen in app store (iOS)

CampaignName.content: Campaign name, as taken from the tracker

ClickTimeHour.content: Attributed click timestamp, rounded to the nearest hour

ConversionDuration.content: Time between click and install or reattribution in seconds

CreatedAtHour.content: Activity timestamp, rounded down to the nearest hour

CreativeName.content: Creative name, as taken from the tracker

DeviceAtlasId.content: ID of the user-agent returned by Device Atlas

EngagedViewBased.content: 1 if attributed to an engaged view, 0 if not

EngagementTimeHour.content: Engagement timestamp rounded to the nearest hour

ImpressionBased.content: 1 if attributed to an impression, 0 if not

ImpressionTimeHour.content: Attributed impression timestamp, rounded to the nearest hour

InstallBeginTime.content: App download began timestamp (Android and Google Play Store only)

InstallTracker.content: 6-/7-character long Adjust tracker token for a user's first attribution source

InstallTrackerName.content: Name of a user's first attribution source

InstalledAtHour.content: Install (i.e., first app open) timestamp rounded to the nearest hour

IsEngagedView.content: 1 if the impression is considered an engaged view by the partner, 0 if not

IsGooglePlayStoreDownloaded.content: Indicating if an app downloaded from Google Play Store or not

IsServerToServer.content: 1 if server to server activity, 0 if not

IsServerToServerBased.content: 1 if attributed to a server to server engagement, 0 if not

LastTracker.content: 6-/7-character long Adjust tracker token of a reattributed user's previous tracker

LastTrackerName.content: A reattributed user's previous tracker name

NetworkName.content: Network name, as taken from the tracker

OutdatedTracker.content: 6-/7-character long Adjust tracker token for outdated trackers in updated attributions

OutdatedTrackerName.content: Encoded tracker name prior to attribution update

ReattributedAtHour.content: Reattribution timestamp, rounded to the nearest hour

ReceivedAt.content: timestamp Adjust server learned about activity (click, session, event)

ReferralTime.content: User landed on app Play Store page timestamp (Android and Google Play Store only)

RejectionReason.example: Anonymous+traffic; Distribution+outlier; Too+many+engagements; Engagement+injection; Invalid+signature; Malformed+advertising+id

SanEngagementTimes.content: JSON payload of unix timestamp of SAN engagements

StoreAppId.content: Store App ID filled in Adjust dashboard(App store, Google Play, Amazon store etc)

TimeToReinstall.content: Time between latest app uninstall and subsequent reinstall in seconds

TimeToUninstall.content: Time between app install (or latest reinstall) and subsequent uninstall in seconds

UninstalledAt.content: Uninstall timestamp (estimation based on last session time)

FbDeeplinkAccountId.content: The account_id value received from FB in deeplinks

FbDeeplinkAdId.content: The ad_id value received from FB in deeplinks

FbDeeplinkAdgroupId.content: The adgroup_id value received from FB in deeplinks

FbDeeplinkCampaignId.content: The campaign_id value received from FB in deeplinks

FbDeeplinkCampainGroupId.content: The campaign_group_id value received from FB in deeplinks

FbInstallReferrer.content: Full FB install referrer, in decrypted format

FbInstallReferrerAccountId.content: The "account_id" value from the FB install referrer

FbInstallReferrerAdGroupId.content: The "adgroup_id" value from the FB install referrer

FbInstallReferrerAdGroupName.content: The "adgroup_name" value from the FB install referrer

FbInstallReferrerAdId.content: The "ad_id" value from the FB install referrer

FbInstallReferrerAdObjectiveName.content: The "ad_objective_name" value from the FB install referrer

FbInstallReferrerCampaignGroupId.content: The "campaign_group_id" value from the FB install referrer

FbInstallReferrerCampaignGroupName.content: The "campaign_group_name" value from the FB install referrer

FbInstallReferrerCampaignId.content: The "campaign_id" value from the FB install referrer

FbInstallReferrerCampaignName.content: The "campaign_name" value from the FB install referrer

FbInstallReferrerPublisherPlatform.content: The "publisher_platform" value from the FB install referrer

MetaInstallReferrer.content: Full Meta install referrer, in decrypted format

MetaInstallReferrerAccountID.content: The "account_id" value from Meta install referrer

MetaInstallReferrerAdGroupID.content: The "adgroup_id" value from Meta install referrer

MetaInstallReferrerAdGroupName.content: The "adgroup_name" value from Meta install referrer

MetaInstallReferrerAdID.content: The "ad_id" value from Meta install referrer

MetaInstallReferrerAdObjectiveName.content: The "ad_objective_name" value from Meta install referrer

MetaInstallReferrerCampaignGroupID.content: The "campaign_group_id" value from Meta install referrer

MetaInstallReferrerCampaignGroupName.content: The "campaign_group_name" value from Meta install referrer

MetaInstallReferrerCampaignID.content: The "campaign_id" value from Meta install referrer

MetaInstallReferrerCampaignName.content: The "campaign_name" value from Meta install referrer

MetaInstallReferrerIsClick.content: 1 if it is a click, 0 if not

MetaInstallReferrerPublisherPlatform.content: The "publisher_platform" value from Meta install referrer

GPSAAdSourceEventID.content: Source event id proviced by Newtwork Partners in their reponse to GPSA to register source

GPSAConversionValue.content: Conversion value if the trigger is an event type, equals 0 for installs.

GPSAIsInstall.content: Indicates if the gpsa trigger is install or not

GPSARandomizedTriggerRate.content: Decimal number between 0 and 1 indicating how often noise is applied.

GPSAReportID.content: Event level report identifier in Google Privacy Sandbox

GPSAScheduledReportTime.content: Time until the browser initially scheduled the report to be sent (to avoid noise around offline devices reporting late).

GoogleAdsAdgroupId.content: Google Ads adgroup ID. Google passes this parameter for Display, Search and Video web campaigns. We use this value to create adgroup trackers

GoogleAdsExternalCustomerId.content: Google Ads external customer ID (account ID)

GoogleAdsKeyword.content: Google Ads search keyword. Google passes this parameter for web Search campaigns. We use this value to create Search creative trackers.

GoogleAdsMatchtype.content: Google Ads search keyword and match type. Google passes this parameter for web Search campaigns. We use this value to create Search creative trackers.

GoogleAdsNetworkSubtype.content: Google Ads network subtype. Google does not pass a value when campaign_type is ACI and network_type is Display

GoogleAdsPlacement.content: Google Ads ad placement. Google passes this parameter for web Display campaigns. We use this value to create Display creative trackers.

GoogleAdsVideoId.content: Google Ads video ID. Google passes this parameter for web Video campaigns on YouTube inventory. We use this value to create Video creative trackers.

GoogleAdsWbraid.content: Google aggregated ID for iOS for App to Web measurement

GoogleMarketingPlatformDbmCampaignType.content: The type of the DBM campaign

GoogleMarketingPlatformDbmCreativeId.content: The unique numeric ID of the DBM creative ad unit

GoogleMarketingPlatformDbmExternalCustom.content: The Google Marketing Platform's DBM advertiser identifier

GoogleMarketingPlatformDcmCampaignType.content: The type of the DCM campaign

GoogleMarketingPlatformDcmCreativeId.content: The unique numeric ID of the DCM creative ad unit

GoogleMarketingPlatformDcmExternalCustom.content: The Google Marketing Platform's DCM advertiser identifier

GoogleMarketingPlatformDcmPlacementId.content: The ID of the DCM placement tag

GoogleMarketingPlatformDcmPlacementName.content: The name of the DCM placement tag

PLTVPredictionLabel.content: PLTV prediction label, can be revenue or event token value.

SKTimerExpiration.content: {sk_conversion_value_device_time} + 24hours = future timestamp for the Apple timer expiration

SkCVUpdateActivityKind.content: Type of user activity that triggered the CV update.

SkConversionValueOnDeviceUpdatedAt.content: Time when conversion value was sent to device

SkConversionValueStatus.content: Status of the conversion value on our system: still pending, successfully sent to device, or couldnt be sent to device due to timer or CV window expiration

SkConversionValueUpdatedAt.content: Time the conversion value was set on our system

SkConversionValueWindowExpiration.content: {installed_at} + the user defined CV window = future timestamp for the CV window expiration

SkInvalidSignature.content: A validation of the SKAdNetwork install postback from the ad network. For an invalid postback, the return value is 1. For a valid postback, the return value is 0

SkLastCountersResetRime.content: Timestamp of when the counters used for CV calculation were last reset (triggered by an app reinstall).

SkRegisteredAt.content: This shows when the skadnetwork registration took place

SkSettingsUpdatedAt.content: This shows when the skadnetwork settings were updated

SkadAttributed.content: 1 if the SKAN conversion came from a device that was already attributed to a non-organic channel, 0 if not.

SkAppId.content: The item identifier of the advertised product

SkCampaignId.content: The campaign ID provided when displaying the ad

SkCoarseConversionValue.content: A coarse conversion value which can take on values low, medium, high. Appears if the app provides one, and depending on crowd anonymity tier.

SkConversionValue.content: The conversion value number, which is an integer between 0-63. Note: The conversion-value appears only if the installed app provides it, and if providing the parameter meets Apples privacy threshold

SkDidWin.content: A Boolean flag [0/1] shows whether the engagement was awarded the attribution or if it qualified for it

SkFidelityType.content: A value of 0 indicates a view-through ad presentation; a value of 1 indicates a StoreKit-rendered (click) ad

SkPayload.content: The complete SKAdNetwork payload received from Apple. The URL is encoded in your callbacks, but not in CSV uploads

SkPostbackSequenceIndex.content: The possible integer values of 0, 1, and 2 signify the order of postbacks that result from the three measurement windows. Available for Version 4 and later

SkRedownload.content: A Boolean flag [0/1] showing if the customer redownloaded and reinstalled the app

SkReportingRevenueMax.content: Total tracked revenue for the defined activity does not exceed the specified amount
SkReportingRevenueMax.example: If the revenue range for the conversion value is 5.00 to 10.00, this value will be 10.00.

SkReportingRevenueMin.content: Total tracked revenue for the defined activity is not less than the specified amount
SkReportingRevenueMin.example: If the revenue range for the conversion value is 5.00 to 10.00, this value will be 5.00.

SkSourceAppId.content: The item identifier of the app that displayed the ad. Note: The source app ID appears only if providing the parameter meets Apples privacy threshold

SkSourceDomain.content: The item identifier of the website that displayed the ad.

SkSourceIdentifier.content: Equivalent of campaign ID provided when displaying the ad for SKAD4

SkTransactionId.content: A unique value for this validation; use for deduplicating install validation messages

SkTs.content: A UNIX timestamp (in seconds) of when the original postback was received by the ad network

SkVersion.content: The postback version sent to the ad network

SubscriptionCancelledAt.content: Unix timestamp from when the subscription stops being valid. Cannot be later than the expiration_time. If the subscription transaction fails and cannot be resolved, the value returned will be the expiration_time of the failed transaction. No value shows in the expiration_time placeholder.

SubscriptionEnvironment.content: Returns a boolean; enviroment of the purchase (different from {environment} )

SubscriptionEventSubtype.content: Name of event subtype (looked up by index)

SubscriptionExpirationTime.content: Unix timestamp of the expiration of a valid subscription. The data can be in the past or future.

SubscriptionExpiredTransactionId.content: The previous valid transaction ID - if it's the first transaction, this returns an empty value. If its a failed transaction, this returns the previous valid transaction ID.

SubscriptionOriginalTransactionId.content: The first transaction ID of the product subscription chain.

SubscriptionProductId.content: Bundle id of the iAP; the subscription product type within the app.

SubscriptionPurchasedAt.content: Unix timestamp of any valid purchase

SubscriptionSalesRegion.content: The region code of the Apple store account's registered location; Googles region code is based on the device's physical location.

SubscriptionStore.content: Which store the subscription purchase was triggered from.

SubscriptionTransactionId.content: The value of a valid transaction. Failed transactions return no value. If there is a billing problem, the current transaction ID is returned.

AndroidIdMd5.content: Lowercase Android ID hex MD5 hash

AttStatus.content: App Tracking Transparency Status. Possible values are 0 (Not determined); 1 (Restricted); 2 (Denied); 3 (Authorized); unknown

CostAmount.content: Cost of the user engagement (available for ad spend tracking only)

CostCurrency.content: ISO 4217 currency code of the cost data (available for ad spend tracking only)

CostIdMd5.content: An MD5 hash of the cost ID provided by a network using our ad spend API (available for ad spend tracking only)

CostType.content: The campaign pricing model (available for ad spend tracking only)

CountrySubdivision.content: Device subdivision of country, e.g., state

Deeplink.content: Deeplink URL appended to click URL

EventCostId.content: A unique event cost ID in UUID format, used for CPE for Adjust Ad Spend push API

EventName.content: Event name, as set in the Dashboard

ExternalDeviceIdMd5.content: A hex MD5 hash of a custom value you can assign to a device or user

GlobalSessionCount.content: Number of sessions recorded across entire user lifetime

GpsAdidMd5.content: Lowercase hex MD5 hash of Google Play Store advertising ID

IdfaOrAndroidId.content: IDFA, or Android ID if IDFA is empty

IdfaOrGpsAdid.content: IDFA, or Google Advertising ID if IDFA is empty

IdfaOrGpsAdidOrFireAdid.content: IDFA, or GPS ADID if IDFA is empty, or Fire ADID if IDFA and GPS ADID are empty

IdfvOrGoogleAppSetId.content: IDFV, or Google App Set ID if IDFV is empty

IsImported.content: 1 if user was imported from another attribution partner, 0 if not

IsReattributed.content: 1 if user was reattributed at least once from an earlier source; 0 if user has never been reattributed

LastTimeSpent.content: Length of user's last session, in seconds

MatchType.example: probabilistic_matching; device_tag; reftag; external_click_id; google; facebook

Mcc.content: Mobile country code: three-digit code identifying a device's country. Use with the mobile network code to identify a device's carrier.

Mnc.content: Mobile network code: two-digit code. Use with the mobile country code to identify a device's carrier.

Nonce.content: Random lowercase alphanumeric string (unique per callback)

Partner.content: An extension of the pre-agreed identifier with networks, showing the name of the partner as stored in the Adjust database

PartnerParams.content: Custom partner parameters collected by the Adjust SDK or S2S request and transmitted to third party providers via postbacks

PostalCode.content: Device postal code of IP address

PushToken.content: Push notification token, i.e., registration token (Android), device token (iOS)

PvPassed.content: 1 when purchase verification passed, 0 if not

RandomUserId.content: Random user ID (per device per app)

Reftags.content: JSON list of valid engagement reftags considered for attribution

ReportingCost.content: Cost of the user engagement converted to your app's reporting currency and as reported in the Adjust Dashboard (available for ad spend tracking only)

ReportingRevenue.content: Revenue, as reported in the Adjust Dashboard, in whole currency units

SessionCount.content: Number of sessions recorded by current Adjust SDK

ThirdPartySharingDisabled.content: 1 if third party sharing is disabled, 0 if not

TimeSpent.content: Length of user's current session, in seconds

TrackingEnabled.content: 1 if tracking is enabled, 0 if not

TrackingLimited.content: 1 if tracking is limited, 0 if not

WebUuid.content: Stands for web unique user identifier
